title: For Sale:  MKE 380 concealed carry PPK / Makarov style
postcontent: This is a nice MKE 380 auto pistol. It's a 7+1 capacity.  That's 1 more then the ruger/taurus/diamondback/kel-tec/hellcat style pocket pistols.This is a variant to the Walther PPK  or Makarov pistols. James Bond style. It breaks down and functions just like a PPK/Makarov.  Quick and easy to brake down and clean. This ones made in Turkey and imported by Firearms Center of Victoria Texas. Its small and could be used as a concealed carry pistol but large enough to be comfortable in you hand and accurate. The PPK design features a fixed barrel, meaning the barrel stays attached to the frame when the slide is removed. This ads to the accuracy of the gun. Most pocket pistols or even alot of full size pistol barrels flop around when the slide is open. That means when you fire the gun the barrel could tilt upward while the bullet is leaving the gun. This gun is in very nice condition. Blue slide with a brownish color frame. Comes with a nice leather belt holster. Like I say perfect concealed carry gun. Reliable and accurate so you can carry it and not have to worry if its going to work when you need it. It features a safety/decocker that allows you to keep a round in the chamber with out having to worry. I buy sell and trade, so let me know what you have. I prefer text REDACTED. and let me know which gun you interested in, I have several for sale. email REDACTED I'm asking $295 with the holster.

location: North Carolina, North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
Description

This auction features a New In Box IMI Uzi Model B chambered in 9mm. The firearm was originally chambered in 41AE and we had it converted to 9mm by simply changing the barrels. The barrel was installed and the firearm was tested by a professional . This is a true pre ban, Israeli made, IMI Uzi. The gun is new and in great condition. This auction includes original box (plastic case and cardboard sleeve), one original 20 round 41AE magazine, one 25 round 9mm magazine, two magazine loaders, dummy barrel, 41 AE barrel, sling, sight adjustment tool, manual and promotional materials.

The Israel Military Industries (IMI) Uzi was a revolutionary weapon in that it was the first to use a telescoping bolt design, in which the bolt wraps around the breech end of the barrel. This allows the barrel to be moved far back into the receiver and the magazine to be housed in the pistol grip. The Uzi uses an open bolt, blowback-operated design. The open bolt design exposes the breech end of the barrel, and improves cooling during periods of continuous fire. Used by the Secret Service from the 1960s until the 1990s, the Uzi is known as one of the most compact, yet versatile, personal defense weapons of the past forty years. This Uzi is a new in box pre-ban Model B in that was originally chambered in 41AE and has been converted to fire 9mm. It's been stored and is in excellent condition.

When NoDak Spud started, they didn't have a manufacturing license, so they the receivers were marked DCI (Dan Coonan Industries).
